The FGS calibration pipeline needs to run in a JWST pipeline build 7 anaconda environment on one of the institute's linux servers
(witserv1 in general, telserv1 or telserv2 for testing). 

Install anaconda to run on a linux server at the institute:

SSH into a linux server:
$ ssh -XY [server name]

Start a bash shell (if bash is not your default):
[server name]> bash

Change directories to your Central Store directory:
bash$ cd /user/[username]

Download and install the latest Anaconda for Linux using curl:
(Note -> Need 64 bit Python 2.7)
bash$ curl -OL https://repo.continuum.io/archive/Anaconda2-4.2.0-Linux-x86_64.sh
bash$ bash Anaconda2-4.2.0-Linux-x86_64.sh

This will take a little bit.

Add the anaconda folder to your PATH on the server:
bash$ echo "export PATH=\"/user/[username]/anaconda2/bin:\$PATH\"" >> ~/.bashrc

Log out, log back in to the server, and start a bash shell:
(The conda command works with bash, not tcsh)
bash$ exit
[server name]> exit
logout
Connection to [server name].stsci.edu closed.
$ ssh -XY [server name]
[server name]> bash
bash$

Check that the conda command is available:

bash$ which conda
/user/[user name]/anaconda2/bin/conda

Setting up conda environment for JWST pipeline build 7

bash$ conda config --add channels http://ssb.stsci.edu/astroconda
bash$ conda config --add channels http://ssb.stsci.edu/conda-dev
bash$ conda create -n jwstb7 --file http://ssb.stsci.edu/conda/jwstdp-0.7.0rc/jwstdp-0.7.7-linux-py27.0.txt

To activate environment:

bash$ source activate jwstb7

To deactivate:

bash$ source deactivate


